    {
      "id": 15,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "About Gluetun metrics",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${datasource}"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 31
      },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "Gluetun runs as a native VPN sidecar in the qBittorrent pod but is **not exporting Prometheus metrics** (no scrape target). qBittorrent shares the pod network namespace and routes all traffic through the tunnel, so its **connection status**, **peer connections** and **DHT nodes** are the effective VPN-health indicators. To get native Gluetun metrics, enable its built-in Prometheus server (`HTTP_CONTROL_SERVER`/metrics on :8000) and add a scrape annotation."
      }
